The paper discusses the problem of billion-scale high-dimensional approximate nearest neighbor search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of indexing structures and data compression, which are common techniques in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed systems on a large dataset, which is a common task in databases (cs.DB).
